    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cpb-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out consistent with ASME V&V 40 Table 3 for a Class II device at MRL 2. Validation evidence demonstrates that the CFD model predicts hemolysis index within 8.1 % of experimental measurements across the CPB operating envelope, satisfying the 15 % acceptance criterion. The credibility assessment team unanimously accepts the simulation evidence as sufficient to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump in the CPB application.",
